text.tspan: In this stage, the person generally put their plans into
actions for at least a day or so. By doing this, the person
generally faces new roadblocks and realizes that there is a
night and a day difference between thinking and doing. If
the person continues action phase for about 2-3 month,
then enters the next stage which is called as “maintenance
phase”. For example, an addicted person will not drink
alcohol at all; he/she will deny his/her “drinking buddies”.
